A human-readable summary (not a substitute for the license) is at:

    https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/

Why CC BY-SA
------------
This directory bundles and builds on the CH552 USB / NeoPixel software stack by
Stefan "wagiminator" Wagner (https://github.com/wagiminator), which is published
under CC BY-SA. Because the PadKit firmware is a derivative and combined work of
that stack, the whole firmware directory is distributed under the same license.

What this means for you
-----------------------
  * Attribution — You must give appropriate credit to the original author(s),
    including Stefan Wagner for the CH552 stack (see ATTRIBUTION.md), and to the
    PadKit project, provide a link to the license, and indicate if changes were
    made. The two local modifications to the vendored stack are marked in-source
    with "PadKit local patch vs wagiminator upstream" comment blocks.
  * ShareAlike — If you remix, transform, or build upon this material, you must
    distribute your contributions under the same CC BY-SA 3.0 license.
  * No additional restrictions — You may not apply legal terms or technological
    measures that legally restrict others from doing anything the license permits.

Copyright
